<TEI.2><text><body><div1 type="alphabetic letter" n="A" org="uniform" sample="complete"><entryFree key="Alacrity" type="main" opt="n"><orth extent="full" opt="n">Alacrity,</orth> cheerful promptitude: <cit><quote>I have not that a. of spirit,</quote> <bibl n="shak. r3 5.3.73" default="NO" valid="yes">R3 V, 3, 73</bibl></cit>. <bibl n="shak. tro 4.4.147" default="NO" valid="yes">Troil. IV, 4, 147</bibl>. <bibl n="shak. oth 1.3.233" default="NO" valid="yes">Oth. I, 3, 233</bibl>. Comically used by Falstaff: <cit><quote>I have a kind of a. in sinking,</quote> <bibl n="shak. wiv 3.5.13" default="NO" valid="yes">Wiv. III, 5, 13</bibl></cit>.
</entryFree></div1></body></text></TEI.2>